usage: Fork [<options>]

Launch Fork as a WSL or Windows git client.
- when launched as a WSL     client, use <fork-install-dir>/wsl-settings.json
- when launched as a Windows client, use <fork-install-dir>/win-settings.json

options:
    -h|--help               display help
    --wsl                   launch Fork as a WSL     git client (default if launched from a WSL     shell)
    --win                   launch Fork as a Windows git client (default if launched from a Windows shell)
    
example:
    Fork                    launch Fork as a WSL or Windows git client
    Fork --wsl              launch Fork as a WSL     git client
    Fork --win              launch Fork as a Windows git client
